headline: IonQ to Showcase Quantum Integration at SuperCompute 2025
summary: COLLEGE PARK, Md., November 13, 2025--IonQ (NYSE: IONQ), the world’s leading quantum company, today announced its participation at SuperCompute 2025 (SC25), the premier international conference for high-performance computing (HPC), taking place November 16–21 at the America’s Center Convention Complex in St. Louis, Missouri.

headline: CoreWeave Announces Zero Egress Migration, Unlocking Multi-Cloud Development for AI Workloads
summary: LIVINGSTON, N.J., November 13, 2025--CoreWeave, Inc. (Nasdaq: CRWV), The Essential Cloud for AI™, today announced the launch of its Zero Egress Migration (0EM) program — a true no-egress-fee data migration program — enabling customers to move large-scale datasets from third-party cloud providers directly to CoreWeave’s cloud without technical friction. headline: IBM and Polytechnique Montréal Launch AI Initiative to Strengthen Forestry Supply Chain
summary: IBM (NYSE: IBM) and Polytechnique Montréal today announced a new collaboration through the IBM Impact Accelerator, IBM's pro bono social innovation program that helps nonprofit and government organizations scale AI-powered solutions for communities and systems facing environmental and economic challenges. The project is part of IBM's 2025 cohort focused on sustainably strengthening supply chains.

headline: IBM Study: Chief Data Officers Redefine Strategies as AI Ambitions Outpace Readiness
summary: A new global study by the IBM (NYSE: IBM) Institute for Business Value reveals enterprise data strategies are rapidly evolving as organizations race to scale AI across their business. The findings suggest that while Chief Data Officers (CDOs) are at the helm of this transformation, many say their data is still not ready to unlock AI's full potential.
